          <h3><span class="highlight">Sworn</span> X'hayu Nhokhi</h3>
        <h4>The Sultansworn</h4>
        <img src="http://i.imgur.com/aRHsB4Q.png"></img>
        <p class="letter">How does a Sultansworn get on a pirate a crew? A better question is, how does a Sultansworn end up in a relationship with a pirate captain? That is correct, Captain Saefinn and X'hayu are (much to X'hayu's dismay) a couple. Really, to answer these two questions, we have to look at her history. X'hayu (pronounced Sha'Hayu) grew up as part of a tribe, some bad things happened, she betrayed a few people, joined the Empire, killed her true love and kinded ended up down a road she would later regret. She defected, seeking to do her best to right her wrongs and help people and work against the empire. First she thought she could make it out in The Shroud, scouting imperials and also helping keep them at bay. But her friend - fellow Garlean defector - Steinn had ended up in Ul'dah, was recruited into a pirate crew, then with his riches, left to become an entrepreneur, hiring Ala Mhigan refugees as his staff. Talk about a guilt complex, eh?
  
  He ended up becoming successful and got closer and close to the Syndicate, who didn't favour helping the refugees too much. X'hayu saw an opportunity here to help and would work her ranks and through selfless deed after selfless deed, she managed to attract the attention of the Sultansworn. As we know, the Sultana's heart went out to the refugees and her interests were not too different to X'hayu's. So, she would swear her oath to the Sultana. She kept close connections with Steinn and he kept close connections with his former crew. X'hayu had no qualms about doing things behind the Sultana's back to help Ala Mhigans who needed it and she had no qualms if the Syndicate unknowingly donated. Yep, that is where pirates come in. Steinn's former crew were the pirates of the Wayward Star.
 
For X'hayu, she at times dependedo n the help of the crew and would return the favour. It wasn't until the Garleans came for Steinn and herself that she found herself becoming closer. The crew had her back, they did everything they could and kept her under their protection, despite knowing who she was the terrible things she had done for the empire. It was after the Captain's brother and mother were caught in the crossfire that X'hayu felt truly in debt and had that guilt hanging over her. Instead of letting it break her, she would try to stand by the crew and its captain. But watching Captain Saefinn descend into self-pity, that he let tragedy break him, that she got angry. Watching him drink and punish himself, she didn't like it, she expected the pirate captain to be strong and carry on. It became a relationship of hate and respect. She still respected him, but hated him for turning into the person he had become. He was no longer a great (though idiotic) pirate captain, he was now a drunk, weak and made a plethora of bad decisions to compromise himself and his crew. 
 
But she did not give up. She, and other members of his crew helped him get clean. It was after his becoming clean that actually, they are good for each other. He still irritates her though, because he has one great skill and that is pushing people's buttons. It is no wonder he keeps getting shot.
 
Her place on the crew is that she helps keep them out of trouble in Ul'dah, she helps cover their backs. She has a few conditions, they are protected, but it's not Leathal Weapon and they don't have diplomatic immunity. X'hayu can only do so much. She will also give jobs for the crew in Ul'dah territory and they will usually center around Ala Mhigans. She will also at times command the crew in Saefinn's absence, she has grown familiar enough with their ways and has done plenty to earn it. Including saving the Captain's life on more than one occassion. She also helps keep the Captain in line, which in itself is a big job.
  
She is short tempered and at times angry. These days, she can control her temper better, but that doesn't stop her from giving a sarcastic or bitchy remark. She has overcome some of the hangups that made her so angry in the first place. But do not take that for granted of course. She will also show a gentler side, if her experience or knowledge can help somebody, then she will offer it. She will share her stories, when relevant, but may or may not leave out details, given her past. She would always come to the defence of a member of the crew or somebody in their care, regardless of how she feels about them. Even if she prefers them dead. Her ideal death would be protecting the life of somebody else.</p>
        
