        <h4>The Xaela Mummer</h4>
        <img src="http://i.imgur.com/r5JHIWX.png"></img>
  <p class="letter">Formerly known as <span class="highlight">Yesunova Hotgo</span>, an Au Rau whose life has faced many prejudices, yet, she remains with her head up high and a song in her heart. The world can be a tough place for all, especially as Eorzea has come to know some of its greatest struggles and it boils down to how one learns to deal with those hardships. Some can choose to let it defeat them, some let it break them, some can choose to let it define them, to drive them, and Vhaso? She has chosen to be above it. Not let it change the skip in her step. She remains a caring soul, seeking to try and uplift the spirits of those around here, as she once did for her tribe. 
  
She was first discovered by Strawberry, our baker, Vhaso had been living on the streets and sought to beg and steal to make her way. It was the crew's estate she sought to rob, Berry caught her in the act. Vhaso's stomach rumbled and Berry's immediate reflex was to feed her. Instead of throwing Vhaso back out on the streets with a hard cold message as to why you do not try to rob pirates, she was given a job as a stablehand, looking after chocobos. Being of a Xaela tribe that rode horses, she had been quite familiar with the stables and it would have seen an appropriate job, but chocobos are not horses, nor do they share the same temprement, Vhaso has spent time learning to be diplomatic with our feathery friends, but still gets nipped by Berry's poorly tempered Pudding.
  
Among her tribesfolk, she was among the group of people who would tell stories and sing songs of their ancestors, to help fill the hearts of warriors and hunters with courage. Inspiration to carry on through hard times, as their ancestors did. There would be soft tales, of tender love and hearts broken and of humour and folly and the misfortunes of those who paid no heed to their surroundings or warning.
  
